scenarios.description: 200 interactions covering a broad mix of common household waste items across all major Magdeburg bins (Residual, Bio, Paper, Yellow, Glass) and disposal routes (Bulky, Hazardous, Electrical). Includes moderate repetition.
200 interactions heavily focused on organic waste (Biotonne) items and common contaminants, reflecting Magdeburg's #wirfuerbio campaign challenges. High repetition of problem items.
200 interactions focusing on various small and large electrical appliances, batteries, and lamps, testing knowledge of WEEE regulations and specific disposal routes.
200 interactions focusing on items typically requiring bulky waste collection or disposal as construction waste, testing knowledge of registration, fees, and what's excluded.
200 interactions focusing on common household hazardous waste items, testing awareness of separate collection and safety notes.
